      <exercise xml:id="Ez_10_4_1">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Let <m>g</m> be a function that is differentiable at <m>(-2,5)</m> and suppose that its tangent plane at this point is given by <m>z = -7 + 4(x+2) - 3(y-5)</m>.
            <ol marker="a.">
              <li>
                <p>
                  Determine the values of <m>g(-2,5)</m>, <m>g_x(-2,5)</m>, and <m>g_y(-2,5)</m>.  Write one sentence to explain your thinking.
