      <exercise xml:id="Ez_10_4_2">
        <statement>
          <p>
            In the following questions, we determine and apply the linearization for several different functions.
            <ol marker="a.">
              <li>
                <p>
                  Find the linearization <m>L(x,y)</m> for the function <m>f</m> defined by <m>f(x,y) = \cos(x)(2e^{2y}+e^{-2y})</m>
                  at the point <m>(x_0,y_0) = (0,0)</m>.  Use the linearization to estimate
